<subSubSection id="C32C6559FA53FF9ECBAFB983FEE3FEB9" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBAFB983FD4DFF18" blockId="54.[151,677,151,178]" box="[151,677,151,178]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<heading id="D0C181BEFA53FF9ECBAFB983FD4DFF18" bold="true" box="[151,677,151,178]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECBAFB983FD4DFF18" bold="true" box="[151,677,151,178]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECBD6B98CFD4DFF18" authority="Bartsch &amp; Rehder, 1939" authorityName="Bartsch &amp; Rehder" authorityYear="1939" box="[238,677,151,178]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECBD6B98CFE9AFF1B" bold="true" box="[238,370,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cerodrillia</emphasis>
Bartsch &amp; Rehder, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC952B983FD4DFF18" box="[618,677,152,178]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1939.0">1939</number>
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBAFB9C4FEE3FEB9" blockId="54.[151,1436,222,275]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<typeStatus id="548D8870FA53FF9ECBAFB9C4FF21FF5E" box="[151,201,223,244]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Type</typeStatus>
species, by original designation: 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC927B9C5FC33FF5E" authority="Bartsch &amp; Rehder, 1939" authorityName="Bartsch &amp; Rehder" authorityYear="1939" box="[543,987,222,244]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="clappi">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC927B9C5FD3EFF5E" box="[543,726,222,244]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cerodrillia clappi</emphasis>
, Bartsch &amp; Rehder, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC890B9C5FC33FF5E" box="[936,987,222,244]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1939.0">1939</number>
</taxonomicName>
(Recent, Hawk Channel, Key West, Florida Keys).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32C6559FA53FF9ECBAFB824FDEDFE6F" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBAFB824FDEDFE6F" blockId="54.[151,1436,319,525]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECBAFB824FEF9FEF2" bold="true" box="[151,273,319,344]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
According to Bartsch &amp; Rehder (
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC990B824FD0CFEF2" box="[680,740,319,344]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1939.0">1939</number>
: 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC9CCB824FCC8FEF2" box="[756,800,319,344]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="127.0">127</number>
), shells waxy in appearance, elongate-turreted, with a smooth protoconch that passes directly to adult sculpture, a short anterior channel, strong recurved axial ribs that extend to the suture, a deep anal sinus, a stromboid notch, and faint spiral striations that strengthen on the shell base, strongest on the columella.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32C6559FA53FF9ECBFFB8CBFBE8FDFF" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="key">
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBFFB8CBFAE7FDA6" blockId="54.[151,1436,319,525]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECBFFB8CBFE5FFE42" bold="true" box="[199,439,463,488]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Key characteristics.</emphasis>
The presence of all the following characteristics, in addition to those that define the family, is diagnostic of species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC92CB8EFFD79FDA7" box="[532,657,500,525]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC92CB8EFFD79FDA7" box="[532,657,500,525]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cerodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and separates the genus from other TWA drilliid genera:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBAFBB27FBE8FDFF" blockId="54.[151,1436,572,885]" box="[151,1024,572,597]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECBAFBB27FF4EFDFE" box="[151,166,572,596]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1.0">1</number>
. A stout, fusiform shell (W/L&gt;= 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC90CBB27FD81FDFF" box="[564,617,572,597]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="0.4">0.40</number>
), usually with a short anterior canal;
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32C6559FA53FF9ECBAFBB7BFD6FF91A" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBAFBB7BFD30FD37" blockId="54.[151,1436,572,885]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECBAFBB7BFF40FDD2" box="[151,168,608,632]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="2.0">2</number>
. Axial ribs that usually extend from suture-to-suture, evanesce on the shell base. Ribs may be partially or wholly absent in the sulcus of older specimens;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBAFBBB3FDB7FD6A" blockId="54.[151,1436,572,885]" box="[151,607,679,704]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECBAFBBB3FF4FFD6A" box="[151,167,680,704]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="3.0">3</number>
. Protoconch of 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECA54BBB3FE9DFD6A" box="[364,373,680,704]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1.0">1</number>
¾– 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECAA4BBB3FE42FD6A" box="[412,426,680,704]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="2.0">2</number>
smooth whorls;
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBAFBBD7FE05FC87" blockId="54.[151,1436,572,885]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECBAFBBD7FF40FD4E" box="[151,168,716,740]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="4.0">4</number>
. Spiral microsculpture primarily on shell base and includes incised grooves, threads, or ridges that strengthen anteriorly, strongest on anterior fasciole; remainder of shell surface may have very fine microscopic spiral lines but is usually smooth; and
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBAFBA23FB65FCDF" blockId="54.[151,1436,572,885]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECBAFBA23FF4FFCE5" box="[151,167,824,847]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="5.0">5</number>
. Cup-handle-like varix behind anal sinus (within ¼-turn of outer lip edge, usually closer) such that the base of the mature shell appears lopsided (skewed to the right) when shell is viewed ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBFFBABEFCFFFAAA" blockId="54.[151,1437,932,1856]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECBFFBABEFE2EFC16" bold="true" box="[199,454,933,956]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Nomenclatural notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECAF5BABFFC84FC16" authority="Bartsch &amp; Rehder, 1939" authorityName="Bartsch &amp; Rehder" authorityYear="1939" box="[461,876,932,957]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Lissodrillia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECAF5BABFFDA6FC17" box="[461,590,932,957]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Lissodrillia</emphasis>
, Bartsch &amp; Rehder, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC80CBABFFC84FC16" box="[820,876,932,956]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1939.0">1939</number>
</taxonomicName>
was erected as a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECF85BABFFAD2FC17" box="[1213,1338,932,957]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECF85BABFFAD2FC17" box="[1213,1338,932,957]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cerodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the distinction that it is smaller (than 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC921BAD3FD6AFC4A" box="[537,642,967,992]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="clappi">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC921BAD3FD6AFC4A" box="[537,642,967,992]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">C. clappi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC993BAD3FCCCFC75" box="[683,804,968,992]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perryae">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC993BAD3FCCCFC75" box="[683,804,968,992]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">C. perryae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the species then included) and has no spiral sculpture. The 
<typeStatus id="548D8870FA53FF9ECBF3BAF6FF13FBAE" box="[203,251,1005,1028]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECA5BBAF7FC79FBAF" authority="Bartsch &amp; Rehder, 1939" authorityName="Bartsch &amp; Rehder" authorityYear="1939" box="[355,913,1004,1029]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Lissodrillia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="schroederi">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECA5BBAF7FD8BFBAF" box="[355,611,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Lissodrillia schroederi</emphasis>
(Bartsch &amp; Rehder, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC868BAF7FC61FBAF" box="[848,905,1004,1029]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1939.0">1939</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
also lacks a cup-handle-like varix just behind the anal sinus, an important distinguishing characteristic of 
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC863BD14FC08FB82" box="[859,992,1039,1064]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC863BD14FC34FB82" box="[859,988,1039,1064]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Cerodrillia</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
At the time, Bartsch &amp; Rehder were probably not aware of the significance of the shape and position of the varix as a generic characteristic since they did not include it in their diagnosis of 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC970BD4CFD2DFBDA" box="[584,709,1111,1136]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC970BD4CFD2DFBDA" box="[584,709,1111,1136]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cerodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species in hand were few and some of their specimens had incompletely developed varices and lips as seen in the 
<typeStatus id="548D8870FA53FF9EC836BD67FC98FB3F" box="[782,880,1148,1173]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC8A1BD67FBFAFB3E" box="[921,1042,1148,1172]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="perryae">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC8A1BD67FBFAFB3E" box="[921,1042,1148,1172]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">C. perryae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Kaicher (
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECFB5BD67FB22FB3F" box="[1165,1226,1148,1173]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1984.0">1984</number>
: card 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECE37BD67FAA0FB3F" box="[1295,1352,1148,1173]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="3895.0">3895</number>
) raised 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECBAFBD84FEF0FB12" box="[151,280,1183,1208]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Lissodrillia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECBAFBD84FEF0FB12" box="[151,280,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Lissodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to generic status for 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC93CBD84FC97FB12" authority="Dall, 1887" authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1887" box="[516,895,1183,1208]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Lissodrillia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="simpsoni">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC93CBD84FD18FB1D" box="[516,752,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Lissodrillia simpsoni</emphasis>
(Dall, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC806BD84FC9FFB12" box="[830,887,1183,1208]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1887.0">1887</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
without explanation; Turgeon 
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECFE1BDBBFAFAFB12" box="[1241,1298,1183,1208]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECE19BD84FAB6FB12" box="[1313,1374,1183,1208]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1998.0">1998</number>
: 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECE51BD84FA7CFB12" box="[1385,1428,1183,1208]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="102.0">102</number>
) adopted this change. The elevation of 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC975BDDFFD26FB77" box="[589,718,1220,1245]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Lissodrillia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC975BDDFFD26FB77" box="[589,718,1220,1245]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Lissodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to generic status is support here principally because the group has a different varix and lacks spiral sculpture altogether.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBFFBC17FD6FF91A" blockId="54.[151,1437,932,1856]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECBFFBC17FE6EFA8E" bold="true" box="[199,390,1292,1317]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Similar genera.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECAABBC17FDF8FA8F" box="[403,528,1292,1317]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECAABBC17FDF8FA8F" box="[403,528,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cerodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC83BBC17FBDFFA8E" authority="Bartsch, 1934" authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="1934" box="[771,1079,1292,1317]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Douglassia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC83BBC17FC6BFA8F" box="[771,899,1292,1317]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Douglassia</emphasis>
Bartsch, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC8C3BC17FBDFFA8E" box="[1019,1079,1292,1316]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1934.0">1934</number>
</taxonomicName>
. See under that genus for an explanation of their differences. Some members of two other genera, 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC8ECBC34FB18FAE2" authority="Bartsch, 1943" authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="1943" box="[980,1264,1327,1352]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pseudomelatomidae" genus="Viridrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC8ECBC34FBABFAE2" box="[980,1091,1327,1352]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Viridrillia</emphasis>
Bartsch, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECF80BC2BFB18FAE2" box="[1208,1264,1328,1352]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1943.0">1943</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECE09BC34FED0FAC6" authority="Bartsch, 1943" authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="1943" class="Gastropoda" family="Horaiclavidae" genus="Inodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECE09BC34FA74FAE2" box="[1329,1436,1327,1352]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Inodrillia</emphasis>
Bartsch, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECA38BC4FFED0FAC6" box="[256,312,1364,1388]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1943.0">1943</number>
</taxonomicName>
have an uncanny resemblance to 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC9E9BC4FFCA6FAC7" box="[721,846,1364,1389]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC9E9BC4FFCA6FAC7" box="[721,846,1364,1389]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cerodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Tippett (
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC8FFBC4FFBEBFAC7" box="[967,1027,1364,1389]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1995.0">1995</number>
: 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECF2BBC4FFB9EFAC7" box="[1043,1142,1364,1389]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="134.5" valueMax="135.0" valueMin="134.0">134–135</number>
) illustrates the radula of 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECBAFBC6CFDFDFA3A" authority="Bartsch, 1943" authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="1943" box="[151,533,1399,1424]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pseudomelatomidae" genus="Viridrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="williami">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECBAFBC6CFE84FA3A" box="[151,364,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Viridrillia williami</emphasis>
Bartsch, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECAE5BC63FDFDFA3A" box="[477,533,1400,1424]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1943.0">1943</number>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC969BC6CFC07FA3A" authority="Bartsch, 1943" authorityName="Bartsch" authorityYear="1943" box="[593,1007,1399,1424]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pseudomelatomidae" genus="Viridrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="hendersoni">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC969BC6CFCAFFA3A" box="[593,839,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Viridrillia hendersoni</emphasis>
Bartsch, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC88FBC63FC07FA3A" box="[951,1007,1400,1424]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1943.0">1943</number>
</taxonomicName>
to demonstrate the more appropriate placement of the genus in 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECAF5BC87FD87FA1F" box="[461,623,1436,1461]" class="Gastropoda" family="Turridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Crassispirinae">Crassispirinae</taxonomicName>
. Recently, most of the Crassispiriinae, including 
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECF90BC87FAF6FA1F" box="[1192,1310,1436,1461]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECF90BC87FAF3FA1F" box="[1192,1307,1436,1461]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pseudomelatomidae" genus="Viridrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Viridrillia</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
have been placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECA3EBCA4FC4BFA72" authority="Morrison, 1965 (Bouchet et al., 2011)" authorityName="Morrison, 1965 (Bouchet et al." authorityYear="2011" box="[262,931,1471,1496]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pseudomelatomidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">
Pseudomelatomidae Morrison, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC95FBCDBFD77FA72" box="[615,671,1472,1496]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1965.0">1965</number>
(Bouchet 
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC82EBCDBFCB8FA72" box="[790,848,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9EC866BCA4FC71FA72" box="[862,921,1471,1496]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Earlier, Sysoev, in Taylor 
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECFEEBCDBFAF8FA72" box="[1238,1296,1471,1496]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECE18BCA4FAB4FA72" box="[1312,1372,1471,1496]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="1993.0">1993</number>
: 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECE51BCA4FA7CFA72" box="[1385,1428,1471,1496]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="164.0">164</number>
) listed 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECBD9BCFFFEA5FA57" box="[225,333,1508,1533]" class="Gastropoda" family="Horaiclavidae" genus="Inodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECBD9BCFFFEA5FA57" box="[225,333,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Inodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a crassispirine genus on the basis of its radula teeth. 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECF36BCFFFB92FA57" box="[1038,1146,1508,1533]" class="Gastropoda" family="Horaiclavidae" genus="Inodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECF36BCFFFB92FA57" box="[1038,1146,1508,1533]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Inodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has most recently been provisionally placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECA8EBF1CFA71F98A" authority="Bouchet, Kantor, Sysoev &amp; Puillandre, 2011 (Bouchet et al., 2011)" authorityName="Bouchet, Kantor, Sysoev &amp; Puillandre, 2011 (Bouchet et al." authorityYear="2011" box="[438,1433,1543,1568]" class="Gastropoda" family="Horaiclavidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">
Horaiclavidae Bouchet, Kantor, Sysoev &amp; Puillandre, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECF7CBF13FB93F98A" box="[1092,1147,1544,1568]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="2011.0">2011</number>
(Bouchet 
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECFC7BF13FAD7F98A" box="[1279,1343,1543,1568]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">et al.</emphasis>
, 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECE6CBF1CFA67F98A" box="[1364,1423,1543,1568]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="2011.0">2011</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Although very similar, 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECA8EBF37FDCEF9EF" box="[438,550,1580,1605]" class="Gastropoda" family="Pseudomelatomidae" genus="Viridrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECA8EBF37FDCEF9EF" box="[438,550,1580,1605]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Viridrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has subtle morphological characteristics not seen in any of the known 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECBAFBF54FEFCF9C2" box="[151,276,1615,1640]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECBAFBF54FEFCF9C2" box="[151,276,1615,1640]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cerodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: an anterior fasciole that lacks spiral ridges, the presence of spiral threads or grooves over the entire shell, not just on the shell base, and a protoconch with obsolete riblets that nonetheless leave a wrinkled look. The protoconch of 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECA02BF8CFE5FF91A" box="[314,439,1687,1712]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECA02BF8CFE5FF91A" box="[314,439,1687,1712]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cerodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is always smooth.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32C6559FA53FF9ECBFFBFA7FAB6F8EA" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8936D2FA53FF9ECBFFBFA7FAB6F8EA" blockId="54.[151,1437,932,1856]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECBFFBFA7FE88F97F" bold="true" box="[199,352,1724,1749]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Distribution.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECAD6BFA7FD83F97F" box="[494,619,1724,1749]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECAD6BFA7FD83F97F" box="[494,619,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cerodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the fourth most species rich among TWA 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECFBCBFA7FB1BF97F" box="[1156,1267,1724,1749]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Drilliidae</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECE39BFA7FA96F97F" box="[1281,1406,1724,1749]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECE39BFA7FA96F97F" box="[1281,1406,1724,1749]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Cerodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed throughout the TWA but most have so far been found to occur in the subtropical waters of the northern portion of this region: Gulf of 
<collectingCountry id="F3217642FA53FF9EC939BE1FFDB1F8B7" box="[513,601,1796,1821]" name="Mexico" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, Florida and the 
<collectingCountry id="F3217642FA53FF9EC81BBE1FFC97F8B7" box="[803,895,1796,1821]" name="Bahamas" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Bahama</collectingCountry>
Is. (see general approximate ranges of known species in 
<figureCitation id="130D2A57FA53FF9ECA34BE3CFE77F8EA" box="[268,415,1831,1856]" captionStart-0="PLATE 35" captionStart-1="PLATE 36" captionStartId-0="82.[151,234,1798,1820]" captionStartId-1="84.[151,234,1863,1885]" captionTargetBox-0="[256,1314,195,1750]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1436,1023,1799]" captionTargetId-0="figure@82.[256,1314,195,1751]" captionTargetId-1="figure@84.[151,1436,1023,1838]" captionTargetPageId-0="82" captionTargetPageId-1="84" captionText-0="PLATE 35. Cerodrillia thea (Dall, 1884). Bahama Is., Florida Keys, E Florida and Cuba specimens. Bahama Is. Fig. 1: Bimini Is. (USNM 900139); Figs. 2, 4 – 5: Tenbay Beach, Eleuthera I. (author’s coll.); Fig. 3: Bimini Is. (H. G. Lee coll.). Florida Keys (Monroe Co.). Figs. 6 – 8: Tavernier Key (H. G. Lee coll.); Fig. 9: Boca Chica Key, Florida Keys (author’s coll.); Figs. 10 – 12: Key Largo (USNM 890154); Figs. 13 – 14: Harry Harris Park, Tavernier Key, Florida Keys (author’s coll.); Figs. 15 – 17: Middle Torch Key (E. Shuller coll.); Fig. 18: N shore, Content Keys (H. G. Lee coll.); Figs. 19 – 20: Little Torch Key (USNM 900134); Figs. 21 – 22: Long Key (USNM 900136); Fig. 23: Boot Key, Marathon (EFG 11547). E Florida. Fig. 24: off Stiltsville, Miami, Miami-Dade Co. (USNM 900141); Fig. 25: Peanut I., Palm Beach Co. (H. G. Lee coll.). Cuba. Figs. 27 – 29: Hicacos Peninsula, Matanzas Prov. (ANSP 157724); Figs. 30 – 31: Cardenas Bay, Matanzas Prov. (USNM 411327)." captionText-1="PLATE 36. Cerodrillia yucatecana, new species. Figs. 1 – 3: holotype, off Contoy Light, Quintana Roo, Mexico (USNM 900116). Fig. 1: ventral lateral &amp; dorsal views; Fig. 2: enlarged view of protoconch (not to scale); Fig. 3: apical view, V = varix, L = edge of outer lip. Fig. 4: paratype, Gulf of Mexico (USNM 900133), ventral view." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/263334/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/263335/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Plates 
<number id="3DFE24F5FA53FF9ECA6EBE3CFE77F8EA" box="[342,415,1831,1856]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" value="35.5" valueMax="36.0" valueMin="35.0">35–36</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9ECA8BBE33FDBCF8EA" box="[435,596,1831,1856]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9ECA8BBE33FDBCF8EA" box="[435,596,1831,1856]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">C. brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C364D51FA53FF9EC9B3BE33FCE9F8EA" box="[651,769,1831,1856]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis id="B942EAC0FA53FF9EC9B3BE33FCE9F8EA" box="[651,769,1831,1856]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">C. elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
inhabit southern subtropical waters (southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3217642FA53FF9ECE30BE3CFAB9F8EA" box="[1288,1361,1831,1856]" name="Brazil" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Brazil</collectingCountry>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
